  <h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Process_Description">Process Description</span></h2>
  <p>A key change between ITIL V2 and ITIL V3 has been a new focus on continually improving services and processes. <a class="mw-selflink selflink">Service Reviews</a> are an essential element of "Continual Service Improvement (CSI)". </p>
  <p>The process overview of <a href="/images/itilcsione.jpg"  title="Service-review-itil.jpg">ITIL Service Review (.JPG)</a> shows the key information flows. </p>
  <p>&#160;</p>
  <h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Sub-Processes">Sub-Processes</span></h2>
  <p>No sub-processes are specified for <a class="mw-selflink selflink">ITIL Service Review</a>. </p>
  <p>&#160;</p>
  <h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Definitions">Definitions</span></h2>
